        <td class="NewsText" style="font-size: 15px">The <a href="edubuntu">Edubuntu</a> team, along with other members of the Ubuntu official editions, published a development snapshot for the projects' upcoming 26.04 release. The new beta previews technologies which will appear in the upcoming long-term support (LTS) release. The Edubuntu <a href="https://discourse.ubuntu.com/t/edubuntu-26-04-lts-beta-released/79207">release announcement</a> shares highlights for the community edition: "<span class="Quote">This release includes GNOME 50. Edubuntu Installer completely rewritten from the ground up in Python with dual GTK 4 and Qt 6 UI backends. The application automatically detects your desktop environment and launches the appropriate interface. It also includes a new Cockpit module for web-based remote administration of Edubuntu’s age-group configuration. Translations are available for 21 languages including Arabic, Chinese (Simplified), Czech, Estonian, French, German, Hindi, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Latvian, Lithuanian, Dutch, Polish, Portuguese, Brazilian Portuguese, Russian, Slovak, Spanish, Turkish and Ukrainian.</span>" Additional information is provided in the Ubuntu <a href="https://documentation.ubuntu.com/release-notes/26.04/">release notes</a>. Download: <a href="https://cdimage.ubuntu.com/kubuntu/releases/26.04/beta/kubuntu-26.04-beta-desktop-amd64.iso">kubuntu-beta-26.04-desktop-amd64.iso</a> (4,906MB, <a href="https://cdimage.ubuntu.com/kubuntu/releases/26.04/beta/SHA256SUMS">SHA256</a>, <a href="https://cdimage.ubuntu.com/kubuntu/releases/26.04/beta/SHA256SUMS.gpg">signature</a>, <a href="https://cdimage.ubuntu.com/kubuntu/releases/26.04/beta/kubuntu-26.04-beta-desktop-amd64.iso.torrent">torrent</a>, <a href="table.php?distribution=kubuntu&amp;pkglist=true&amp;version=26.04-beta#pkglist">pkglist</a>), <a href="https://cdimage.ubuntu.com/lubuntu/releases/26.04/beta/lubuntu-26.04-beta-desktop-amd64.iso">lubuntu-beta-26.04-desktop-amd64.iso</a> (3,809